  <compounddef id="group__cython__group" kind="group">
    <compoundname>cython_group</compoundname>
    <title>Cython Python Bindings</title>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Python interface to AnalysisG via Cython. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>AnalysisG provides comprehensive Python bindings through Cython, allowing users to leverage the full power of the C++ framework from Python.</para>
<sect1 id="group__cython__group_1cython_overview">
<title>Overview</title>
<para>The Cython bindings are organized as follows:</para>
<para><table rows="7" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Location   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Contents    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/core/</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Core class bindings (Analysis, templates)    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/events/</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Pre-built event templates    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/graphs/</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Pre-built graph templates    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/models/</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Pre-built neural network models    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/selections/</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Pre-built selection templates    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/metrics/</computeroutput>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Pre-built metric templates   </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__cython__group_1cython_structure">
<title>File Structure</title>
<para>Each Cython module consists of:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>.pxd</computeroutput> file: C++ declarations (similar to header files)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>.pyx</computeroutput> file: Python implementation and bindings</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__cython__group_1cython_core">
